President Muhammadu Buhari is currently meeting with governors of All Progressives Congress (APC) at the presidential villa, Abuja. The meeting is coming ahead of the March 26th National Convention of the ruling party, which had been beset by crises in recent times. The meeting is not unconnected with the effort by the President to ensure that all cracks in the ruling party are cemented before the exercise. The governors are being led in the meeting by the Chairman of the party’s National Caretaker Committee and governor of Yobe State, Mai Mala Buni. More details later… YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE We Have Not Had Water Supply In Months ― Abeokuta Residents In spite of the huge investment in the water sector by the government and international organisations, water scarcity has grown to become a perennial nightmare for residents of Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital. This report x-rays the lives and experiences of residents in getting clean, potable and affordable water amidst the surge of COVID-19 cases in the state…Buhari meets APC governors  Buhari meets APC governors Selfies, video calls and Chinese documentaries: The things you’ll meet onboard Lagos-Ibadan train The Lagos-Ibadan railway was inaugurated recently for a full paid operation by the Nigerian Railway Corporation after about a year of free test-run. Our reporter joined the train to and fro Lagos from Ibadan and tells his experience in this report…Buhari meets APC governors  Buhari meets APC governors ORITAMEFA BAPTIST MODEL SCHOOLS, (OBMS), IBADAN 
